<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1031181-but-milton-friedman-and-the-other-shock">&quot;But (Milton) Friedman and the other shock therapists were also guilty of the oversimplification, basing their belief in the perfection of market economies on models that assumed perfect information, perfect competition, perfect risks markets. Indeed, the case against these policies is even stronger than the one Klein makes.&quot; Do you agree with Nobel Prize Winning Economist Stiglitz&#39;s quote?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1031181'><a id="like_count_community_question_1031181" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1031181?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1237300.The_Shock_Doctrine">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1031181-but-milton-friedman-and-the-other-shock">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1031181-but-milton-friedman-and-the-other-shock">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/16868576-johan"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1359325311i/16868576._UX100_CR0,43,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/16868576-johan">Johan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">What does even perfect mean in these instances?<br/><br/>Friedman must have been thrilled when approached by Pinochet, for the first time someone was showing in<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">What does even perfect mean in these instances?<br /><br />Friedman must have been thrilled when approached by Pinochet, for the first time someone was showing interest in implementing his untested ideas.<br /><br />Thinking that (economic) decisions are taken purely based on available information is already there nonsense. Then to take step to say that perfect information would lead to a perfect market economy is simply delusional.<br /><br />So basing a wide range of (macroeconomic) policies on such notions is nothing but irresponsible. <br /><br />So I yes, I agree with Stiglitz on this one.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
