    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1095777759" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1095777759" />
    <a title="Kevin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35434974-kevin"><img alt="Kevin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607981917p2/35434974.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1095777759?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin" href="/user/show/35434974-kevin">Kevin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35434974-kevin?shelf=critique-imperialism-america">critique-imperialism-america</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1095777759" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13969096090554538861"><b>Shocking, to liberals…</b><br/><br/><b>Preamble</b>:<br/>[2020 Update on old reviews] <br/>--My ultimate hope with influential (large platform, accessible), progressive public intellectuals like Klein is: <br/>1) they inspire as many as possible (given their specific audiences/reach) and <br/>2) their audiences do not get stuck on this one thinker&apos;s ideological progression, but continue to explore for themselves. <br/>--Klein has been successful with engaging especially the North American/Western “center-left”, what I think of as “<b>default l</b></span>
  <span id="freeText13969096090554538861" style="display:none"><b>Shocking, to liberals…</b><br /><br /><b>Preamble</b>:<br />[2020 Update on old reviews] <br />--My ultimate hope with influential (large platform, accessible), progressive public intellectuals like Klein is: <br />1) they inspire as many as possible (given their specific audiences/reach) and <br />2) their audiences do not get stuck on this one thinker's ideological progression, but continue to explore for themselves. <br />--Klein has been successful with engaging especially the North American/Western “center-left”, what I think of as “<b>default liberals</b>” since they are casual observers who start in what they see as the “middle ground” (centrism). They can relate to “liberal”/ “progressive” sides on the surface issues that have first been <b>framed/contextualized</b> by the mass (corporate) media and political theatre. In other words, the boundaries of debate have already been set by corporate power (paraphrasing <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2476.Noam_Chomsky" title="Noam Chomsky" rel="nofollow noopener">Noam Chomsky</a>). <br />--Note: this is in contrast to “<b>devoted liberals</b>”, those in power or influence who actively use the liberal ideology (individual freedoms while the economy is enclosed by the powerful, forcing more people to participate in wage labor where there is no economic democracy) to secure power. This is further contrasted from “<b>leftists</b>”/“radicals”. Liberals are not leftists. <br />--Klein is relatable to the privileges of Western default liberals, with her 1999 breakout <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/928935.No_Logo_Taking_Aim_at_the_Brand_Bullies" title="No Logo Taking Aim at the Brand Bullies by Naomi Klein" rel="nofollow noopener">No Logo: Taking Aim at the Brand Bullies</a> starting from Western consumerism. However, it took her 8 years to progress to the "Rise of Disaster Capitalism", and 15 years to progress to "Capitalism vs. The Climate" (<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/21913812.This_Changes_Everything_Capitalism_vs__The_Climate" title="This Changes Everything Capitalism vs. The Climate by Naomi Klein" rel="nofollow noopener">This Changes Everything: Capitalism vs. The Climate</a>)... <br /><br /><b>The Useful</b>:<br />--The amazing Mexie applies the insights of this book: <br />1) “There is no such thing as a Natural Disaster, Part I: Hurricane Katrina”: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://youtu.be/ZjsvG595Gf8">https://youtu.be/ZjsvG595Gf8</a><br />2) “There is no such thing as a Natural Disaster, Part II: Puerto Rico”: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://youtu.be/czJ9dYoHaZc">https://youtu.be/czJ9dYoHaZc</a><br /><br /><b>The Bridge to Cross</b>: <br />--Let us not get stuck on the bridge, folks. There is only a “<b>rise</b>” of Disaster Capitalism from the sheltered perspective of those who have benefited from the post-WWII economic boom, which was only possible after the endless Great Depression was “resolved” by the most destructive world war in human history. This “<b>creative destruction</b>” destroyed much of existing stagnant capital, and revolutionized the technologies/social relations for the next capitalist boom (in the form of the US’s <b>military industrial complex</b>). Once the boom subsided and the crisis of capitalism (stagnancy in a system that requires growth, where <i>nothing gets done unless there are sufficient profits for the few</i>) emerged again, <b>Neoliberalism</b> became the strategy to revitalize profitability. <br />…Neoliberalism meant the scraps from the table that the Western “<b>middle class</b>” received from the boom had to be withdrawn, and thus “Disaster Capitalism” has come closer to home.<br /><br />--However, “Disaster Capitalism” is a constant tool of capitalism:<br />1) <b>Primitive Accumulation</b> was essential to set up the capitalist markets required for capitalist production/accumulation in the first place! This meant kicking serfs/peasants off traditional lands, i.e. the Enclosures (creating the <b>land market</b>), where the dispossession of their means of production/subsistence meant the only other social relation that offered survival was to sell their labor (creating the <b>labor market</b>). <br />-accessible intro: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36490332.Talking_to_My_Daughter_About_the_Economy_or__How_Capitalism_Works___and_How_It_Fails" title="Talking to My Daughter About the Economy or, How Capitalism Works - and How It Fails by Yanis Varoufakis" rel="nofollow noopener">Talking to My Daughter About the Economy: or, How Capitalism Works - and How It Fails</a><br />-deeper dives: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1107750.The_Invention_of_Capitalism_Classical_Political_Economy_and_the_Secret_History_of_Primitive_Accumulation" title="The Invention of Capitalism Classical Political Economy and the Secret History of Primitive Accumulation by Michael Perelman" rel="nofollow noopener">The Invention of Capitalism: Classical Political Economy and the Secret History of Primitive Accumulation</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/403846.Caliban_and_the_Witch_Women__the_Body_and_Primitive_Accumulation" title="Caliban and the Witch Women, the Body and Primitive Accumulation by Silvia Federici" rel="nofollow noopener">Caliban and the Witch: Women, the Body and Primitive Accumulation</a><br /><br />2) The <b>entire history of capitalism</b>, from dark satanic mills and brutal laws against vagrancy (to enforce wage labor) in “advanced” capitalist regions to colonialism destroying competition and enforcing <s>underdevelopment</s> over-exploitation to the slave trade. <br />-accessible intro to unfair trade (but don't get stuck on this bridge either!): <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1032019.Bad_Samaritans_The_Myth_of_Free_Trade_and_the_Secret_History_of_Capitalism" title="Bad Samaritans The Myth of Free Trade and the Secret History of Capitalism by Ha-Joon Chang" rel="nofollow noopener">Bad Samaritans: The Myth of Free Trade and the Secret History of Capitalism</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7859.Late_Victorian_Holocausts_El_Ni_o_Famines_and_the_Making_of_the_Third_World" title="Late Victorian Holocausts El Niño Famines and the Making of the Third World by Mike Davis" rel="nofollow noopener">Late Victorian Holocausts: El Niño Famines and the Making of the Third World</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6617037.Debt_The_First_5_000_Years" title="Debt The First 5,000 Years by David Graeber" rel="nofollow noopener">Debt: The First 5,000 Years</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2690635.Perilous_Passage_Mankind_and_the_Global_Ascendancy_of_Capital" title="Perilous Passage Mankind and the Global Ascendancy of Capital by Amiya Kumar Bagchi" rel="nofollow noopener">Perilous Passage: Mankind and the Global Ascendancy of Capital</a><br />-there are plenty of literature around Capitalism and Slavery, ex. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14894629.The_Half_Has_Never_Been_Told_Slavery_and_the_Making_of_American_Capitalism" title="The Half Has Never Been Told Slavery and the Making of American Capitalism by Edward E. Baptist" rel="nofollow noopener">The Half Has Never Been Told: Slavery and the Making of American Capitalism</a><br /><br />3) Even <b>during the post-WWII economic boom</b>, the US empire was busy implementing “Disaster Capitalism” on parts of the world struggling to liberate themselves from colonialism and industrialize/re-industrialize to become alternatives/competition!<br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/53054943.The_Jakarta_Method_Washington_s_Anticommunist_Crusade_and_the_Mass_Murder_Program_that_Shaped_Our_World" title="The Jakarta Method Washington's Anticommunist Crusade and the Mass Murder Program that Shaped Our World by Vincent Bevins" rel="nofollow noopener">The Jakarta Method: Washington's Anticommunist Crusade and the Mass Murder Program that Shaped Our World</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/54169138.Washington_Bullets" title="Washington Bullets by Vijay Prashad" rel="nofollow noopener">Washington Bullets</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/78130.Killing_Hope_U_S__Military_and_C_I_A__Interventions_Since_World_War_II" title="Killing Hope U.S. Military and C.I.A. Interventions Since World War II by William Blum" rel="nofollow noopener">Killing Hope: U.S. Military and C.I.A. Interventions Since World War II</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/44771267.The_Management_of_Savagery_How_America_s_National_Security_State_Fueled_the_Rise_of_Al_Qaeda__ISIS__and_Donald_Trump" title="The Management of Savagery How America's National Security State Fueled the Rise of Al Qaeda, ISIS, and Donald Trump by Max Blumenthal" rel="nofollow noopener">The Management of Savagery: How America's National Security State Fueled the Rise of Al Qaeda, ISIS, and Donald Trump</a><br />-<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17609.The_Darker_Nations_A_People_s_History_of_the_Third_World" title="The Darker Nations A People's History of the Third World by Vijay Prashad" rel="nofollow noopener">The Darker Nations: A People's History of the Third World</a><br />-global South playlist: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSQhQoKnYhTXceMPfa4MYyJjnm5ScFIZ_">https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list...</a></span>
